@node XYGADGET_CONSTRUCTOR "xygadget_plugin: Constructors / Destructor"

   @{BG shine}Constructor@{BG back}

      @{b}xygadget(@{"tags" link XYGADGET_TAGS}=NIL:PTR TO tagitem)@{ub}

      For creating a new plugin object use for example:
      @{FG fill}
      DEF xygadget:PTR TO xygadget_plugin
      NEW xygadget.xygadget([..., TAG_DONE])
      @{FG text}

@endnode

@node XYGADGET_METHODS "xygadget_plugin: New Methods"

   @{b}set(@{"tag" link XYGADGET_TAGS}, value)@{ub}

      By calling this method it's possible to change attributes
      at runtime. You can use all tags with the S flag set.
      This method can also be used before the GUI is created and when
      the window is closed.
      Value is a LONG and contains the argument for the used tag.
      @{FG fill}
      Example:
      DEF xygadget:PTR TO xygadget_plugin
      ...
      NEW xygadget.xygadget([..., TAG_DONE])
      ...
      xygadget.set(PLA_XYGadget_Disabled, TRUE)
      ...
      @{FG text}

   @{b}value,check:=get(@{"tag" link XYGADGET_TAGS})@{ub}

      This method is the counterpart to set. All tags with G flag
      can be used. Argument is the tag you want to get. Return values
      are the requested value and as second a boolean value. So if
      check is FALSE the used tag can't be get.

      @{FG fill}...
      value,check:=xygadget.get(PLA_XYGadget_Disabled)
      ...@{FG text}

      After this:
       value=TRUE
       check=TRUE

@endnode

@node XYGADGET_TAGS "xygadget_plugin: Tags"
 The letters [ISG] show you when the tags can be used.
 I = @{"Initalisation" link XYGADGET_CONSTRUCTOR}
 S = @{"Set Method" link XYGADGET_METHODS}
 G = @{"Get Method" link XYGADGET_METHODS 18}


    @{FG shine}PLA_XYGadget_Text@{FG text}          [ISG]

        The text contents of the gadget in the PLUGIN.


    @{FG shine}PLA_XYGadget_Disabled@{FG text}      [ISG]

        Disable or enable the gadget. Setting this tag causes the
        gadget to become disabled; it is ghosted.

        Boolean; defaults to FALSE.


@endnode

